commText: Welcome back.. Some good news for the SRH fans - there is no dew at the ground unlike in the games at Ahmedabad where batting became easier in the second innings due to dew. The groundstaff still used the ropes to ensure the outfield is completely dry. The powerplay is going to be crucial as the new ball will come on. SRH have a huddle before taking the field. Jaiswal and TKC stride out to the middle. Bhuvi has the new ball. There's one slip in place. We are ready to go..

Trent Boult: Understood what we're coming up against. A batting line-up that likes to hit boundaries. There was a mixture of boundaries and a mixture of wickets, which is a little bit unusual. We took wickets throughout the whole game and that restricted them to a score that we are pretty confident about. You always try to be aggressive, the hardest thing is to adapt to the wicket. The last two wickets we played on have probably been the best two of the whole tournament which is great for this time of the tournament. We hung in there nicely as a group and the way we finished at the death along with the spinners in the middle, we have restricted them to a nice total. Those guys (Avesh and Sandeep) have been doing an amazing job, adapting to whatever surface we have come up against. Avesh has been bowling beautifully for us the whole tournament. Sandy (Sandeep) is a very experienced bowler and he showed his skill tonight. Only half the job done, we are looking forward to the chase.

21:20 Local Time, 15:50 GMT: 176 is the magic number for Rajasthan Royals tonight. They would have taken that when Samson won the toss and put Sunrisers Hyderabad in. Boult did the damage in the powerplay by picking up three wickets but Tripathi's 15-ball 37 ensured that Hyderabad got off to a flying start. The game slowed down as the field spread and the ball got older. The bowlers found bowling into the pitch and taking pace off was the way to go. Avesh and Sandeep were brilliant at that as they didn't Klaasen to get on with things. The keeper-batter curbed his natural game and got to a fifty but was dismissed in the penultimate over. Only 12 runs came off the last two overs and that might be a telling factor. But SRH have got a blueprint as to how to bowl on this wicket and that will make the chase interesting. Back soon..

Avesh Khan to Cummins, out Unadkat Run Out!! Cummins started to walk even before Avesh delivered the ball, it is a good length delivery outside off, Cummins has a swing and miss. The ball was just past the wide marker but Cummins had moved across his stumps as he attempted that big shot and hence it was not given as a wide. Unadkat tried to steal a bye but Avesh collected the ball and hit the target at the bowler's end to catch him short. Unadkat run out (Avesh Khan) 5(2) [4s-1]
Avesh Khan to Cummins, THATS OUT!! Run Out!!

SRH review! The wide is not given on the field so Cummins decides to send it upstairs. The third umpire too deems it a legal delivery. They also check for a run-out and Unadkat is short of his crease. OUT
Avesh Khan to Unadkat, 1 run, full and outside off, Unadkat drives to sweeper cover and it is only a single

Avesh Khan to Unadkat, FOUR, haha! This was comical and no wonder the players involved had a smile on their face. Unadkat premeditated he's going to play the lap or scoop, so Avesh goes full and outside off, Unadkat gets into a tangle but manages to lap it over backward square leg
Jaydev Unadkat, right handed bat, comes to the crease

Avesh Khan to Shahbaz Ahmed, out Caught by Dhruv Jurel!! This was a hit-me delivery and Shahbaz has missed out. Full toss around knee height, Shahbaz kneels down and heaves it towards long-on, Jurel runs in and takes a good catch. He got it high on the bat and hence could not get the timing right. Just 1 run and a wicket so far in this over. SRH need to touch 180. Shahbaz Ahmed c Dhruv Jurel b Avesh Khan 18(18) [6s-1]
Avesh Khan to Shahbaz Ahmed, THATS OUT!! Caught!!
Avesh Khan to Shahbaz Ahmed, wide, bouncer that is too short and too high, Shahbaz allows it to sail over and collects the wide
Avesh Khan to Shahbaz Ahmed, no run, I0$ short of length delivery, Shahbaz is early into the pull and misses. Two dots to start the final over
Avesh is bowling from round the wicket
Avesh Khan to Shahbaz Ahmed, no run, I0$ nails the yorker outside off, Shahbaz backed away and made it more difficult to connect
Avesh Khan [3.0-0-21-2] is back into the attack

Sandeep Sharma to Cummins, no run, I0$ off-pace short ball, Cummins shuffles and attempts the ramp but the ball never arrived. What an over, just 6 runs and the wicket of Klaasen. Sandeep bowls out - 4-0-25-2
Sandeep Sharma to Shahbaz Ahmed, 1 run, angled outside off, Shahbaz shuffles and slaps it straight to long-on
Sandeep Sharma to Cummins, 1 run, I0$ slower ball on leg, Cummins nudges it to mid-wicket and settles with a single
Sandeep Sharma to Cummins, no run, now the slower short ball, Cummins waits and is still early into the cut shot, fails to connect

Sandeep Sharma to Cummins, FOUR, that was neatly done. Sandeep nails the yorker around off, Cummins opens the bat face and squeezes it past a diving Samson. Not sure he meant it to go that fine but he's not complaining..
Pat Cummins, right handed bat, comes to the crease

Sandeep Sharma to Klaasen, out Bowled!! Whoa! What a moment in this game. Sandeep has knocked over a set Klaasen with 11 balls still to go in the innings. The reactions in the two dugouts tells the story - joy in one and disappointment in the other. Perfect yorker from Sandeep, Klaasen also gestures that it dipped on him as he walks off, the ball sneaks under his bat and hits the base of leg-stump. Klaasen b Sandeep Sharma 50(34) [6s-4]
Sandeep Sharma to Klaasen, THATS OUT!! Bowled!!
Sandeep Sharma [3.0-0-19-1] is back into the attack
Boult to Shahbaz Ahmed, no run, I0$ full pitcher around off, Shahbaz pushes it to the right of Boult and he makes the stop
Boult to Shahbaz Ahmed, wide, slower bouncer sprayed down leg, Shahbaz has a go but is nowhere close to connecting

Boult to Klaasen, 1 run, fifty for Klaasen. This is a top knock and a very important one from SRH's point of view. He does not celebrate as the job is not done. Shahbaz walks across and shakes his hand. Full delivery on the pads, Klaasen flicks to deep mid-wicket and is content with a single
Boult to Shahbaz Ahmed, 1 run, slower ball bowled into the wicket, Shahbaz steers it to short third and Klaasen gets back on strike
Boult to Shahbaz Ahmed, 2 runs, backs away and Boult nails the yorker, jammed to the vacant mid-wicket region and the pair race back
Boult to Klaasen, 1 run, slower short of length delivery, Klaasen slaps it wide of long-off and wanted a second, not there
Back over the wicket
Boult to Klaasen, wide, goes for the yorker outside off, but sprays it past the marker, Klaasen can't squeeze it out and umpire signals a wide
Round the wicket now

Boult to Klaasen, SIX, smashed! You have to be spot on with your length against Klaasen. This was neither yorker nor short, right in the arc and Klaasen has a free swing of the bat, smokes it flat and straight back over Boult
Trent Boult [3.0-0-32-3] is back into the attack
When will Klaasen start taking more risks? There is not a lot of batting left after this duo. Cummins can hit the ball long but you would not want him batting for 3 overs. Boult to bowl out first..
Ashwin to Shahbaz Ahmed, 2 runs, 14 from the over. Short and outside off, Shahbaz cuts late towards backward point and there's a fumble by Boult, allowing the batters to come back for the second
Ashwin to Klaasen, 1 run, worked into the mid-wicket pocket and this time the pair settle with a single
Ashwin to Klaasen, 2 runs, once more tucks it gently into the vast open spaces on the leg-side and races back for the second. Sensible batting so far..
Ashwin to Klaasen, 2 runs, carrom ball darted into leg-stump, Klaasen works it with soft hands into the leg-side and scampers back for the second
Ashwin to Shahbaz Ahmed, 1 run, quicker and drifts in, Shahbaz leans forward and nudges it to long-on

Ashwin to Shahbaz Ahmed, SIX, that's an excellent shot. Shahbaz has to take Ashwin on here. This was fraction short and he's quick to pounce, rocks back and nails the pull to deep mid-wicket. He hit it to the shorter side and had no problems clearing the rope
Ravichandran Ashwin [3.0-0-29-0] is back into the attack

Four overs left. Chahal has bowled out and rest of them have an over each. Ashwin might bowl this over as Shahbaz will be on strike and leave the last 3 overs to the pacers. Avesh has come back superbly after going for 13 runs in his first over.
Avesh Khan to Shahbaz Ahmed, 1 run, I0$ short of length around off, Shahbaz knocks it wide of cover and retains strike
Avesh Khan to Shahbaz Ahmed, no run, I0$ short of length delivery, Shahbaz backs away and swings across the line,
Avesh Khan to Klaasen, 1 run, I0$ fullish delivery outside off, Klaasen eases it to long-off

Most sixes conceded in an IPL edition 31 – Mohammed Siraj in 2022 30 – Yuzvendra Chahal in 2024* 30 – Wanindu Hasaranga in 2022 29 – Dwayne Bravo in 2018 28 – Yuzvendra Chahal in 2015 28 - Tushar Deshpande in 2023

Avesh Khan to Shahbaz Ahmed, 1 run, I0$ back of a length and once again Shahbaz looks to heave it to the leg-side, gets an inside edge to square leg and manages to get off strike
Avesh Khan to Shahbaz Ahmed, no run, I0$ not quite short and hence Shahbaz cannot time it cleanly, mistimed pull to mid-wicket
Avesh Khan to Shahbaz Ahmed, no run, back of a length and angled in, Shahbaz tucks it with soft hands to mid-wicket
Avesh goes round the wicket

Avesh Khan to Shahbaz Ahmed, wide, bouncer right at the batter, Shahbaz takes it on instinctively and is beaten on the top-edge. Looks like SRH have reviewed for the height on that. Clearly over the head and the decision will be overturned

Highlights (11-15 overs) - Chahal varies his pace to bowl a quiet over - Sandeep uses the slower balls to good effect - Just 8 runs off the over despite Klaasen's six off Chahal - Avesh removes Nitish and Samad off successive balls
Chahal to Klaasen, no run, flatter and at the stumps, Klaasen knocks it to the left of Chahal
Chahal to Shahbaz Ahmed, 1 run, full toss on off, Shahbaz closes the bat face and the leading edge rolls wide of cover
Chahal to Shahbaz Ahmed, wide, I0$ quicker, shorter and outside off, Shahbaz attempts to cut and misses, called a wide
Chahal to Shahbaz Ahmed, no run, throws it outside off, Shahbaz angles it to backward point
Chahal to Shahbaz Ahmed, 2 runs, googly on leg-stump, Shahbaz nudges it to the vacant mid-wicket pocket and races back for the second
Chahal to Klaasen, 1 run, dipping full toss and Klaasen chips it to long-on, goes on the bounce

Chahal to Klaasen, SIX, this is typical Klaasen. He picks the length so quickly there, this was not all that short but Klaasen camps on the back foot, uses his height and launches the pull over wide long-on
Chahal to Klaasen, wide, drifted down leg, Klaasen looks to help it along the way and fails to connect
Shahbaz Ahmed, left handed bat, comes to the crease

Timeout! Avesh has turned the game on its head once again. SRH were rebuilding after losing Head in the 10th over but the RR bowlers kept the pressure on and didn't allow the runs to come freely which led to Nitish's wicket and that in turn got Samad as well. Klaasen remains the key for SRH and he has to bat deep if they are to get a competitive total. The impact sub has been used - Shahbaz comes in for Head.

Avesh Khan to Abdul Samad, out Bowled!! Cleaned! Avesh did it against RCB and is doing it now against SRH. He picked up Patidar and DK in the Eliminator only for the latter to survive, here there's no need of the umpire or review as he cleans up Samad. God length delivery and it tails in a touch, Samad's feet are stuck to the crease and he has a tenative prod, leaving a gap for the ball to sneak past the inside edge and hit the top of off-stump. Abdul Samad b Avesh Khan 0(1)
Avesh Khan to Abdul Samad, THATS OUT!! Bowled!!
Abdul Samad, right handed bat, comes to the crease

Avesh Khan to Nitish Reddy, out Caught by Chahal!! Nitish's picks out Chahal perfectly. Third catch for the leggie and all have come around the same region. Avesh has his first wicket and Rajasthan continue to push Hyderabad back. This was full and outside off, Nitish went for the reverse sweep and connected cleanly, but Chahal was placed perfectly. There were two fielders inside the ring behind square on the off-side - Ashwin was almost at a fly slip region and Chahal around the short third region, the ball flies to the latter and Chahal makes no mistake. Nitish Reddy c Chahal b Avesh Khan 5(10)
Avesh Khan to Nitish Reddy, THATS OUT!! Caught!!
Avesh Khan to Klaasen, 1 run, full and hint of inward tail, Klaasen ekes out an inside edge onto the pad and the ball rolls to the leg-side
Avesh Khan to Nitish Reddy, 1 run, nails the yorker outside off, Nitish squeezes it to deep backward point

Avesh Khan to Nitish Reddy, no run, SRH lose a review. Needless! This was the frustration from Nitish. He is not been able to get going and now tries to a reverse lap, Avesh spears the yorker outside off and Nitish lets it pass thinking he will get a wide, but he had moved a long way across the stumps and the ball was also close to him when he let it go
SRH review! It is for a non-wide call. Nitish went up immediately. But he has moved a long way across his stumps. The onfield decision will stay. Not a wide
Avesh Khan to Nitish Reddy, 2 runs, full toss outside off, Nitish slices it towards sweeper cover and picks up a brace
Avesh Khan [1.0-0-13-0] is back into the attack
Chahal to Nitish Reddy, 1 run, 90.2kph, bends his back leg does Nitish Reddy to drive this full delivery to sweeper cover
Chahal to Klaasen, 1 run, 88.7kph, Klaasen moves leg-side and Chahal follows him with a full delivery. Flicked to deep midwicket
Chahal to Klaasen, SIX, 89.8kph, incredible shot. Flat leggie and Klaasen slightly backs away and manufactures a lot of power despite going back. Thumped over wide long-off for a maximum
Chahal to Klaasen, no run, 91.5kph, quicker one, Klaasen rocks back to punch it to extra cover
Chahal to Klaasen, no run, 87.1kph, Klaasen backs away, Chahal sees that and bowls it wide of off. No shot offered
Chahal to Klaasen, no run, 88kph, drifting in on the pads, Klaasen misses the flick to get hit on the pad
Sandeep Sharma to Nitish Reddy, no run, another good over for RR! 104.4kph, slow and short, Nitish Reddy misses the pull as he's early into his shot. The ball goes to the keeper on the bounce
Sandeep Sharma to Klaasen, 1 run, 122.5kph, yorker and Klaasen has managed to flick it away to deep midwicket
Sandeep Sharma to Klaasen, no run, 107.2kph, Klaasen cuts hard but picks out the man at extra cover
Sandeep Sharma to Klaasen, wide, bouncer with not much pace, Klaasen half-ducks under it. Wided for height
Sandeep Sharma to Nitish Reddy, 1 run, 127.3kph, back of a length delivery, shuffles across and punches through point. Powell is quick to get to the ball and the batters settle for a single
Sandeep Sharma to Klaasen, 1 run, 125.9kph, chopped to long-off. Klaasen wanted to hit it much squarer
Sandeep Sharma to Klaasen, 2 runs, 122.9kph, width on offer, cut away to deep point
Last three overs: 10 runs | 1 wicket | 0 boundaries.
Chahal to Nitish Reddy, no run, 85.2kph, another googly, Nitish Reddy goes back in his crease to push it to cover
Chahal to Nitish Reddy, no run, 83.3kph, googly, Nitish Reddy gets forward to block and inside-edges onto his back leg
Chahal to Nitish Reddy, no run, 78.5kph, very slow. Nitish Reddy is early to flick and gets a leading edge that falls short of the forward-diving Jaiswal at extra cover
Travis Head vs Sandeep Sharma in IPL Inns: 3 Runs: 25 Balls: 21 Dismissals: 2 SR: 119.0
Chahal to Klaasen, 1 run, 96.7kph, pushed through quick around leg, Klaasen moves leg-side to flick it to midwicket
Chahal to Klaasen, 2 runs, 91.6kph, leg-lined, whipped between long-on and deep midwicket
Chahal to Klaasen, no run, flat on leg, Klaasen tickles it to short fine leg
Nitish Reddy, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Yuzvendra Chahal [1.0-0-11-0] is back into the attack

Highlights (6-10 overs) - Head gets a couple of fours away to end the powerplay - Avesh goes for 13 in his first over - Klaasen wastes no time in going after Chahal - Ashwin bowls a quiet over, just 4 runs - Sandeep gets the big wicket of Head

Sandeep Sharma to Head, out Caught by Ashwin!! Head screams in anguish as soon as he makes contact. Very similar to Tripathi's dismissal. Slower ball into the surface, Head makes room to try and go over short third man. But the lack of pace results in a miscue. Comes off the inner edge of the bat and it's a straightforward catch for Ashwin at short third man. Big wicket! Head c Ashwin b Sandeep Sharma 34(28) [4s-3 6s-1]
Sandeep Sharma to Head, THATS OUT!! Caught!!
Sandeep Sharma to Head, no run, 105.2kph, shortened length, Head shapes to pull it over midwicket, doesn't connect as the ball scoots under his blade
Sandeep Sharma to Klaasen, 1 run, 109.4kph, slow and full outside off, drilled to long-off
Sandeep Sharma to Klaasen, no run, 109.2kph, slower ball outside off, Klaasen cuts straight to extra cover
Sandeep Sharma to Head, 1 run, 125.8kph, length ball wide of off, Head makes room to slap it to sweeper cover
Sandeep Sharma to Klaasen, 1 run, 118.8kph, pace off, back of a length, punched to long-off
Sandeep Sharma [1.0-0-10-0] is back into the attack
Ashwin to Klaasen, 1 run, 93.6kph, nudged to square leg for a single. Excellent over from Ashwin. In fact, this is the first over of the innings where SRH have failed to score a boundary
Ashwin to Head, 1 run, low full toss and Head drives to long-off
Ashwin to Klaasen, 1 run, 98.8kph, carrom ball, Klaasen stays back to knock it to long-off
Ashwin to Head, 1 run, 99.3kph, quicker one, Head cuts it to sweeper cover

Ashwin to Head, no run, 87.5kph, slower and Head gets down to sweep hard. Beaten by the extra bounce. Samson appeals for caught behind but nothing from the bowler. The ball wasn't too far away from the sticks either
Ashwin to Head, no run, 96.2kph, round the wicket, flat ball on a short of length, punched to the right of the bowler and Ashwin makes a diving stop
Ravichandran Ashwin [2.0-0-25-0] is back into the attack
Spin from both ends
Chahal to Head, 1 run, 89.3kph, more air, leg-lined, flicked to deep midwicket
Chahal to Klaasen, 1 run, 90.2kph, Chahal bowls this wider, cut to sweeper cover

Chahal to Klaasen, SIX, 93.3kph, this is what Klaasen can do! Bash sixes off the back foot. Not too short, Klaasen is quick to rock back, clear the front leg and pummel it over deep midwicket for an 81m six. Chahal has a smile on his face

Most runs in the powerplay in an IPL edition 467 - David Warner, 2016 (SR: 150.16) 402 - Travis Head, 2024 (SR: 209.37)* 382 - Adam Gilchrist, 2009 (SR: 165.36) 374 - Jos Buttler, 2022 (SR: 133.57) 373 - Virat Kohli, 2024 (SR: 161.47)

Bowlers with 100-plus T20 wickets in the Powerplay 128 - David Willey 118 - Bhuvneshwar Kumar 101 - Trent Boult *where ball-by-ball data is available
Chahal to Head, 1 run, 95.1kph, now it's Head's turn to punch off the back foot. A single to long-off
Chahal to Klaasen, 1 run, 94.3kph, flat ball that skids off the deck, Klaasen punches it to long-off off the back foot
Chahal to Head, 1 run, 85.9kph, full on the stumps, Head drives hard to long-off
Yuzvendra Chahal, right-arm leg break, comes into the attack

Strategic timeout! Despite losing wickets, SRH continue to attack. Boult struck in the very first over to remove the dangerous Abhishek Sharma. Tripathi came out all guns blazing but he was deceived by a slower ball from the Kiwi pacer who also nipped out Markram in the powerplay. Head was kept quiet for five overs but the Aussie has struck three fours and a six in the last two overs.
Avesh Khan to Head, 1 run, low full toss, Head goes hard on the drive and outside-edges towards third man and Sandeep doesn't err on this occasion

Avesh Khan to Head, FOUR, 138.8kph, length ball outside off, Head crouches a bit to slash it away. Goes to the left of third man quickly off the outer half and Sandeep Sharma misfields which results in a boundary. Avesh won't be a happy man

Avesh Khan to Head, SIX, 138.3kph, this is what he tried off the previous ball as well. Same ball, same shot and he's middled this one. With his front leg off the ground, Head stylishly flicks this short of length ball over deep backward square leg for a 70m six
Avesh Khan to Head, no run, 138.9kph, short of length ball on leg, Head looks to flick it away with one leg off the ground. Goes towards short fine leg off the thigh pad and Klaasen gets sent back
Avesh Khan to Klaasen, 1 run, 139.6kph, skiddy length ball on off, Klaasen stays in his crease to force it to deep point
Avesh Khan to Head, 1 run, 132kph, short of length outside off, cut over point. There's protection in the deep
Avesh Khan, right-arm fast medium, comes into the attack
Sandeep Sharma to Head, 1 run, 124kph, knocked to long-on. End of an eventful powerplay - 8 fours | 3 sixes | 3 wickets
Sandeep Sharma to Head, FOUR, fuller than a length outside off, Head gets down low to cut. The ball hits the turf and eludes the diving point fielder to his right. Sandeep has his hands on his head
Sandeep Sharma to Head, no run, 126.4kph, makes room to cut, but fails to find the gap through point
Sandeep Sharma to Head, FOUR, first boundary for Head! 123.5kph, pitched up delivery, Head clears his front leg and smashes it over mid-off. Gets the necessary elevation
Most wickets in the powerplay in IPL 2024 12 - Trent Boult* 10 - Bhuvneshwar Kumar 9 - Mitchell Starc 8 - Vaibhav Arora 8 - Khaleel Ahmed
Sandeep Sharma to Klaasen, 1 run, over the wicket, full on middle and leg, flicked to deep square leg
Sandeep Sharma to Head, leg byes, 1 run, round the wicket, angled in on the pads, Head misses the glance and the ball dribbles to short fine off his pad
Sandeep Sharma, right-arm fast medium, comes into the attack
Heinrich Klaasen, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Rahul Tripathi vs Trent Boult in IPL Inns: 6 Runs: 29 Balls: 24 Dismissals: 3 Avg: 9.66 SR: 120.8

Highlights (1-5 overs) - Abhishek v Boult in the first over - 0, 6, 4, 2, W - There's some extra bounce in the surface - Tripathi takes Ashwin on - 4, 4, 6 - Tripathi is dropped by Samson, Ashwin the unlucky bowler - Boult ends Tripathi's knock, gone for 15-ball 37 - Boult has a third as Markram goes for 1

Boult to Markram, out Caught by Chahal!! Third wicket for Boult! Markram is distraught as he departs cheaply. Fails to make a mark after coming into the XI. 139.3kph, Markram sees the width outside off on this length ball and throws his arms at it. Gets an outside edge that goes to short third man where Chahal crouches low to take another catch. Markram c Chahal b Boult 1(2)
Boult to Markram, THATS OUT!! Caught!!
Boult to Head, 1 run, 136.3kph, in-seaming short of length ball following a backing away batter. Head gets an inside edge onto his thigh and the ball rolls into the off-side
Boult to Markram, 1 run, 137.8kph, length ball, turned to deep midwicket
Aiden Markram, right handed bat, comes to the crease

Most Wickets in the first over of an IPL edition 8 - Trent Boult in 2020 7 - Trent Boult in 2024* 7 - Trent Boult in 2023 6 - Bhuvneshwar Kumar in 2016 6 - Trent Boult in 2022 6 - Mohammad Siraj in 2023

Boult to Tripathi, out Caught by Chahal!! The slower ball does the trick! 103.1kph, slower ball into the wicket, Tripathi hops and tries to periscope it towards third man. The ball, however, hits the inner edge and goes straight to short third man where it's a dolly for Chahal. Tripathi c Chahal b Boult 37(15) [4s-5 6s-2]
Boult to Tripathi, THATS OUT!! Caught!!
Boult to Tripathi, FOUR, 123.5kph, length ball wide of off, Tripathi waits on the back foot and expertly cuts it between backward point and short third man. Tripathi is dealing in boundaries!
Boult to Tripathi, SIX, wow! Tripathi is on fire. 135.4kph, Tripathi moves across towards off and brings his wrists into play to whip this length ball over long leg

Ashwin to Tripathi, 1 run, was that a stumping chance? Beautiful delivery from Ashwin who deceives the batter in the flight. Carrom ball, Tripathi looks to go over the off-side and gets beaten on the outside edge as the ball spins away. Samson fails to gather it cleanly and the batters sneak a run via byes. Head dives to make his ground. Given as runs, so it might have been a drop!
Ashwin to Tripathi, no run, stump-to-stump line, Tripathi defensively pushes it back to the bowler
Ashwin to Tripathi, SIX, Tripathi is going after Ashwin! A full toss from the veteran, Tripathi moves across and sweeps it high and over fine leg for a 66m six
Ashwin to Tripathi, FOUR, 99.4kph, quicker and closer to off, Tripathi stays back and plays late. Opens the bat-face at the very last moment to guide it fine of short third man. Deft!
Ashwin to Tripathi, FOUR, 95.2kph, carrom ball, full in length and Tripathi thumps it over mid-off. Gets under the ball after backing away and bending his back leg, then gets the necessary elevation
Ashwin to Head, 1 run, 96.5kph, slides on with the arm, Head hangs back and knocks it towards mid-on
Boult to Tripathi, FOUR, 138.2kph, finds the gap on this occasion! Fuller than a length and Tripathi punch-drives through cover point and the ball speeds away to the fence
Boult to Tripathi, no run, 136.5kph, slanted across the right-hander, Tripathi cuts well but he can't beat backward point who makes a diving stop to his left
Boult to Head, 1 run, 139.8kph, pitched up, driven towards mid-off for a quick single

Boult to Abhishek Sharma, out Caught by Kohler-Cadmore!! Boult strikes in the first over, again! 138.7kph, back of a length ball that comes quicker than the batsman expects it to. Bit of extra bounce as well and that results in a mishit. Abhishek Sharma stays in his crease to heave it away and the ball hits him high on the bat. The bottom hand comes off the handle as well and the ball lobs up towards backward point where TKC takes a safe catch. Eventful opening over! Boult to Abhishek Sharma, 2 runs, 136.6kph, short of length ball around off and middle, Abhishek Sharma opens his bat-face to steer it behind square on the off-side
Boult to Abhishek Sharma, FOUR, Boult hurls it full, hint of away swing, Abhishek Sharma slightly moves leg-side to drive it straight down the ground. The timing is exquisite

Boult to Abhishek Sharma, SIX, 132.1kph, Boult pulls his length back, Abhishek Sharma spots it and stands tall to authoritatively pull it over deep midwicket for a 71m six. Super shot to get off the mark
